President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of Florida and authorized federal aid to assist in recovery efforts after severe storms and flooding from July 2-7, 2013. The funding will be available to state and local governments, as well as certain nonprofit organizations, for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in Holmes, Walton, and Washington counties. Additionally, federal funding will be provided for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Terry L. Quarles has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.